text_blocks.content: 1 Instruction No. 26: Count Six: Sex Trafficking of an Individual Under the Age of 18 - First Element

The first element of Count Six which the Government must prove beyond a reasonable doubt is that Ms. Maxwell knowingly recruited, enticed, harbored, transported, provided, or obtained a person, Carolyn. The terms "recruited," "enticed," "harbored," "transported," "provided," and "obtained" have their ordinary, everyday meanings. In considering whether Ms. Maxwell has acted knowingly, please apply the definition of "knowingly" previously provided to you.
